The Ibadan zonal office of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has arraigned a Permanent Secretary in the Oyo State Ministry of Agriculture, Alhaji Rasaq Kolawole, in court for allegedly defrauding Ibikunle Alonge of the sum of N4.4 million. Kolawole was arraigned yesterday before Justice Aderonke Aderemi of the Oyo State High Court on a count charge of obtaining money under false pretence. A statement signed by the EFCC Head, Media and Publicity, Dele Oyewale, said Alonge had written a petition to the EFCC, in which he accused the top public servant of fraudulently collecting the money from him as part payment for a piece of land situated at the Alabata Olosoko area of Moniya, Ibadan. Alonge further alleged that it was after he had paid Kolawole the money on or about October 2, 2018 that he got to know the land actually belonged to one Mrs. Ali (now deceased). Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here The amount, allegedly paid to the Permanent Secretary through Pastor Adeyemi Fabayo, was said to be part payment of the total cost price of 11 and a half plots of land situated at Alabata Olokoso. All efforts to retrieve his money from the defendant, Alonge added, were unsuccessful. Kolawole pleaded not-guilty to the charge. In view of his plea, the prosecuting counsel, Dr Ben Ubi, prayed the court for a date for the commencement of trial. Justice Aderemi admitted the defendant to bail on self-recognition and adjourned the matter till June 24 and 25, 2020 for trial.  EFCC re-arraigns Ladoja, others over N4.7bn alleged fraud 'Fake native doctor', 2 others remanded over fraud N11.5billion fraud:Â  Absence of witness stalled Akala, 2 others trial